  31:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       Alternatively to the normal programming mode, a DMA channel can be programmed by a list of tr
  32:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       linked-list (list of Node items). Each node is defined by its data structure.
  33:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       Each node specifies a standalone DMA channel.
  34:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       When enabled, the DMA channel fetch the first linked-list node from SRAM (known as head node)
  35:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       next linked list node will be fetched and executed. This operation is repeated until the end 
  36:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       linked-list queue. Optionally, the linked-list can be linear where the last linked-list queue
  37:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       to another queue node or circular where the last linked-list node is linked to any linked-lis
  38:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
